Q： What is the maximum number of exchanges involving any particular element during selection sort?
What is the average number of exchanges involving an element?


A：

1) Each time we found a minimum,we need to exchange it with the current. For a size N array,
we need to find minimum N-1 times, so maximum number of exchanges is N-1.

2)  average number of exchanges involving an element N exchanges, N items, so avg= 1. WHY???

